parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake module can cause the vehicle to experience extended stopping distances, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS engages at low speeds
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle vibrates when applying the brakes
the stopping distance is increased
the vehicle pulls to one side when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
rusted brake lines
abnormal brake fluid loss.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped or worn-out rotors can cause the brake pedal to vibrate, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Warped or worn-out rotors
brake pedal vibration
abnormal brake noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake sensors can cause the ABS to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: ABS engages at low speeds
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle vibrates when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause the wipers to stop functioning, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially during inclement weather.
symptoms: The windshield wipers stop working
the wipers work intermittently
the wipers do not start
the wipers quit working during heavy rain or snow
the wipers only work when the engine is turned off and then restarted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering pump loses power
the pulley shaft breaks off at the impeller
the vehicle is difficult to steer
especially at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become unstable and difficult to control, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering goes into "full mode" at high speeds
making small movements of the steering wheel equivalent to large turns
the vehicle jerks around in the lane
the steering wheel feels loose or unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear box can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or unstable
the vehicle pulls to one side when turning
the steering shaft yoke wears
causing an off-center steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the steering column or shaft can cause unusual noises, vibrations, or feelings of slipping or sliding when turning, which can be distracting and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Noise in the steering wheel when turning
the steering wheel feels like it's slipping or sliding when turning
the SIR coil in the steering column is faulty.
